caption: Fully enjoyed our dinner at El Che in Chicago. Staff was super friendly, helpful and accommodating. Had an amazing encounter with the chef who explained their elaborate grilling set up that was open to the dining room. Dinner was delicious with interesting menu options and all cooked to perfection. Would go back there next time i visit for sure.

Leigh, our waitress, was terrific! She expertly guided us through the menu. The swordfish, steak and quail were all delicious. We especially loved the sides of broccoli, squash and olives. The dessert--shortbread cookies with gelato--was yummy! The hostess was very friendly, as were all employees. We sat at a hightop in the bar area and loved it. Thanks for a great evening!
Killer meats!
Great place!
Food was so delicious. Certainly worth going back to.
Super delicious. The staff was helpful and kind. The bill was average for the menu.
Open flame cooking at its best. Chef is a wizard and everything is *FIRE*. Don't pardon the pun.
Great protien.  Great wine.  Great service!
Great Food
you won't be disappointed in the menu and service. definitely worth a return trip.
I give this spot two thumbs up. Fast and courteous service. It has a nice feel to it.
I love visiting here. The staff was very sociable and kind. Prices were decent. Makes me feel like I am back in Sacramento.
The staff was very helpful and observant. I see why this place has so many good reviews.
My favorite dinner overall on my vacations.
Super tasty. The service was very helpful and welcoming. Prices were fair for the quality of the food. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I loved.
Great restaurant and service. Easy to get to from the downtown and worth the 15 dollar uber.  Steak were cooked to perfection!  Definitely add to your list.

Everything, everything was on point! From the ease of making the reservation, to the host's and initial contact, Q on service,  Matt on management, and yo. The actual food?! Outstanding.  Presentation, flavor,  texture, and portion sizes were all exceptional. Highly recommend!  And I too will be back no doubt.

Great, just great. This is a fantastic place to get a wonderful steak and sit along the sidewalk on a beautiful night. Our meal was perfect, service was excellent (not pushy or on us every 5 minutes) and desert was incredible. Definably give it a try.
I was super full. The service was friendly and sociable. The bill was decent. Feels like a cafe in Phoenix that I enjoyed visiting.

Bought 4 steaks from El Che Meat & Provisions, which is Che's new meat market available any day that they're open. The steaks are prime from Whittingham Meats, and they far superior to what you can get at the grocery store. I ordered a filet, two NY strips, and a ribeye--all delicious. I also purchased green chimichurri, red chimichurri, and salsa criolla, which are must have with the steaks. Worth the trip.

Worst empanadas I’ve ever tried! I’m not sure these guys have ever tasted an Argentinian empanada. I suggest making a quick trip to Miami, at the very least, to try the real deal. The provoleta also arrived burnt and the toast could only be described as charred. Melting cheese and making toast should be as basic a task for a professional kitchen as it gets but they totally ducked it up! I couldn’t bring myself to order an entree after the empanadas and the provoleta.

Was not impressed at all. Never heard of a “parrillada” being served on a plate. The meat was cold and salty. It was way too expensive to receive cold/salty meat. The waitress only came to my table once, which wasn’t appreciated either.

This place is obviously one of the finest place in the area. Whenever I come to this place I am incredibly happy. They manage their very high  standard service and the topmost level of cooking  they offer. You will be always satisfied with this restaurant. Very  recommended.
Amazing food and excellent service

This restaurant has authentic Argentinian food. The ambiance is wonderful. The food is presented beautifully. The steaks as expected were excellent. Servers and staff were friendly and attentive. Worth checking out when in the west loop.

We met with friends at this spot for lunch. we heard about this place from a lot of people.  Well, it was very successful. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we felt excellent. The meal was great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Keep it up.
Excellent service, atmosphere and food. Try the empanadas they are fantastic!
The food was very good but a little bit greasy for me as I do not eat that amount of beef. Attention was great and also the atmosphere.
El Che was great! We got the empanada and frites appetizers, wedge salad, short rib and the El Che steak. Everything was delicious and had unique flavors. We will definitely be back!

Always enjoy dinners here. Realized I have never written a review despite having been over 5 times, and in a city like Chicago where the options are endless, that’s meaningful! Great wine list and meat and seafood entrees.
Great atmosphere, good drinks, the parrillada it's outstanding and the service was awesome

My girlfriend took me out for my 8th birthday (I'm a leap baby) and the experience in total was phenomenal. We had the chefs table tasting menu and all the dishes were expertly executed. Chef John and Alex made for a memorable experience of perfectly paired foods and libations. Being right up against the grill while the rest of Chicago was chilly made this a comfortable and entertaining dining experience. They described the dishes thoroughly and offered great conversation between courses. It felt like we were visiting close friends for dinner that we hadn't seen in years. I can't recommend this experience enough! We'll be back without a doubt!

I couldn't say enough good things about El Che. My boyfriend and I went to El Che for the Chef's Counter and it was a such an incredible experience. The food was so delicious and made with a lot of attention and care it really came through. We got to sit right in front of the hearth and talk with Chef John. We also got to talk with Alex, the sommelier, who did an amazing job pairing our food with the dishes Chef prepared for us. What Chef John does here is very unique here, and I hope this is something they continue to do here at the restaurant. Nothing beats good food and good people.
(Translated by Google) Very good, roasted fussion. More does not have the essence of Argentine barbecue!  (Original) Muy bueno ,asado fussion. Más no tiene la escencia del asado argentino !!!!
Best restaurant in Chicago. Insanely good food and great service. The steak is good enough to convince a vegan to change their mind for a meal.
Food was on par.

Celebrated a friends birthday during restaurant week. Came in early for Happy Hour and  stayed for dinner. I wasn’t a fan or the meat infused Vodka; the bartender was nice is removing it from my bill. The food was good as were the other cocktails that I had.

Brought a friend from out of town. The food, drinks, and service were all stellar.  We had the grilled oysters, veal sweetbreads, gnocchi, rack of lamb, and the broccoli.  I would eat that lamb every day if my budget could allow it. And the sweetbreads were cooked and prepared perfectly.
Wonderful experience at the hearth table. Everything was delicious and the chef was friendly and funny.

I arrive at this special place once a month since I like the special air that is outline this place. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably cordial and professional. The service is absolutely quick. Needless to say, the food you eat is perfect. I have been there often and I was always pleased. The rate is honest. I highly recommend this restaurant to to everybody.

We went here for the first time on valentines day. It was really cold that night, and the temperature inside was also pretty cold. That's the only complaint I have about the dining experience. We ordered the empanadas for our starter and they were really good, but small. My husband got a ribeye steak and beef short ribs. He liked the steak but loved the ribs. He also got the asparagus which he was amazed by. I am vegetarian so I ordered the gnocchi and as the waitress recommended, I mushroom sauce instead. It was literally the best gnochi I have ever had. I got the broccoli too and it was fantastic as well. I had to take most of it to go, but it reheated even better. We got the flan but that was the only thing I felt like was a ripoff. It was a great taste and texture, but it was so small and the sprinkles confused me LOL so weird and inconsistent with the meal. Highly recommend. I can't wait to return.

We decide to go all in on the chef tasting and drink pairing for our Valentine's Day celebration. It was a fantastic experience, not only because of the food and drink, but the people. From the GM who committed to provide a warm and comfortable experience with the drink selection, to the guys over that hot hearth who put in the time, detail and effort to create the dining journey. The mix of seafood and beef in each of the dishes was amazing. The openness to questions and conversations made this a unique and comforting experience.
Was honestly not that impress with the steak I had. Definitely more on the salty side, but it has a great vibe and the drinks are solid.

Absolutely fantastic! They take such simple food and fill it with flavor, it is unique, the drinks are great, and the steak is as to be expected at an Argentinian steakhouse. Yes, it is pricey, but it is a great date night spot that will leave your taste buds satisfied.

Hands down one of the best meals I’ve ever eaten. If you can swing it, I highly recommend reserving the Chef’s Table. I usually hate going out to steakhouses for dinner; I’m somewhat snobby about preparation, particular cuts, quality, so I’ve taken the time learning to do it right at home. Steakhouses, including all of your favorites in Chicago, are usually not worth the expense to me. El Che is worth it. El Che is more than worth it. For a fixed price, not including drinks, we were served a salad, empanadas, beef short ribs (which are meant to be chewy and fatty, by the way), fried cheese on toast with bone marrow, oysters, shrimp, broccoli, pork chops, ribeye, more bone marrow, more bread toasted with more marrow, sweet breads, blood sausage, chorizo, and three different desserts. It’s 8:30am the next day, and I still can’t get out of bed. Chef John messed me up real good. I honestly was in such awe of the presentation, that I don’t recall many of the details, but one my favorites that I did catch was the oysters, which we baked with kettle chips and hot sauce. The ribeye was cooked perfectly, which is to say salted and over an open flame.  We had the opportunity to meet Chef John Manion, who spent a good deal of time talking to our table about chips and the importance of dips. He’s clearly a man after my own heart, and I’m very pleased we had the chance to eat at his table. I will 100%, without question, be returning for another meal.

We had some drinks, Parrillada (upgraded to bone-in ribeye) and pomme puree. The inside of our medium rare steak was cold. They said the steak could get cold since it’s medium rare. But it wasn’t even room temperature it was more like, it was in the fridge cold. Besides than that, the drinks and the pomme puree was really good.

Having traveled to Argentina a few years ago, I am always on the hunt for and craving Argentine food - I dont even consider myself to be a huge fan of steak but there is something particularly delightful about the Argentine preparation.  This restaurant brought my back to my lovely vacation with their authentic flavors and dishes.  Even if you have never been to Argentina, it is worth a visit to see what all the fuss is about!
Awesome Happy Hour!
Parrillada is recommended

Very positively surprised by our experience here. Yes it’s a steakhouse, but it doesn’t have the haughtiness of many of the upscale Chicago steakhouses. Instead, the focus is on really high quality Argentinian food and service that is both friendly and correct, as well as slightly frivolous, this not creating a super stuff experience.  The empanadas were absolutely fantastic, the broccoli side was amazing, and the lomo was superbly cooked. Definitely recommend.
Food is really great. I recommend the bone marrow.

We came to this spot for dinner. we heard about this spot from many people.  Well, it was a winning. the crew were so friendly and we felt very good. The meal was great. We loved this restaurant very much and we shall definitely come back again. Highly recommended.

The Filet was cooked perfectly.  The chimichurri that came with it looked like salad dressing,  but was truly amazing. The service was on point. They may be getting a bonus because I was with a great group of guys,  and I feel blessed that the last meal I had with this group (I'm moving) was so fantastic.  Can't go wrong with the Filet!!
Drinks were good, food was cold and average
The service, atmosphere and food were outstanding. It is an expensive restaurant but truly value for money.
Excellent steak.
I only wish I had more stars to give because this place is amazing!
Fantastic service with delicious food and drinks

Let's say you feel like a night out and are craving steak, but you are tired of the monotonous steak scene.  Enter El Che  We tried pretty much everything on the menu and it was aces all around.  Let me put it to you this way, if you are looking for a reason to eat here let it be this.  For centuries man has tried perfecting the cooking of beef over open flames.   El Che may have figured it all out.
Steak was chewy. Overpriced for what you get.
Such a great place! The atmosphere is great and the taste of all of the food from the wood fire is superb! Definitely check this place out if you're in the West Loop area!
Amazing service and great food.
Went for NYE dinner. Excellent service and good. Very nice ambience.  The desserts were amazing!
Great food and atmosphere, we sat at the long table by the kitchen and it was a great experience!
Great food and wine. Fantastic ambiance. Friendly knowledgeable staff. Loved every minute of it. Will be back!!!

I booked a reservation in advanced for a celebration, when I first walked in A women in her Mid 30’s, blonde Host was unwelcoming with her face and actions. Then told me a walk in was going to be seated before me and made it seem like it was going to be awhile and gave no time frame. I ordered the PARRILLADA, excited from The delicious looking pictures. DON’T EVEN WASTE YOUR MONEY ON THAT. The beef ribs, super chewy and the beef sausage was pure rubber. Definitely would choose another steakhouse if that’s your attraction to this place. Bandera for perfect beef ribs !

El Che is a hip little place filled with a beautiful Latin flair! The music and ambiance felt nothing like a bar, but more like chic café somewhere south of the border! Great place for a date! Great service, extremely attentive to the restaurant goers. Our server was helpful with his ability to explain to my wife and l the menu and the specialty's. The steak was good perfectly cooked.  The sided were extremely creative and tasted fantastic (a broccoli dish and a squash dish)! if you like the flame-broiled flavor of beef like I do, you will love it here. I give this happening steakhouse 4.3 Stars. Go check it out, it's worth your time and money!
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Exceptional character, fresh food, great customer service. 5 stars.
I had an awesome experience at this place. We liked the extraordinary environment and the food. The staff members are super friendly. I’m glad we finally managed to visit this spot.

The best meat in chicago. They do know how to serve a stake

My friend and I had a wonderful meal at the Chef's counter. Everything that was prepared was fantastic. The atmosphere, ambiance, and everything about the overall experience made it one of the best dining experiences of our lives. It's perfect for a date night, with just 2 seats right in the action. Chef John was awesome! Special mention of the gnocchi which was phenomenal.

We did the Chef’s Table six course tasting menu and the experience was fantastic. It was really cool sitting at the back counter in front of the grill and watching the chefs work. All of the food was very good and reminiscent of Argentinian steakhouse flavors...but elevated. We ordered the “soft pairing” drink option to go along with the meal, which was also very good. Neither of us drink and are always happy when restaurants offer interesting drink options beyond booze. All of the staff was super friendly and made sure our experience was special. Can not recommend enough and would love to get back to try some of the menu options that we watched the chefs prepare, but were not part of our menu.

Food was pretty good, but service and pricing were not. I suggest a place next to Micigan Avenue that will deliver a great steak or seafood at similar price. The West Loop and other areas near there are overrated...
Great food and atmosphere, we pretty much cleaned our plates
What a treat! El Che offers the best of food, ambiance, and service. You are treated with a rare level of service. There is something for everyone on the menu. Everything is tast!

They don't honor A La Card (the $10 off coupons that are a participating restaurant with). I went to the restaurant ONLY because I had the $10 coupon. I went for dinner before a show at the Lyric, so it happened to be during their happy hour time. We ordered several starters/sides, a couple of drinks, and a steak. Some of those items were discounted because of it being happy hour, however some were not, including the full-price steak. They would not allow me to use the $10 A La Card because of happy hour, despite even one of their items being full-price and qualifying for the coupon (you have to spend $25 to get the $10 off. The steak was $34).
Great steak. Mayan is a great server. They don't have Jameson, which I don't like, so I'm fine with it, but I know that may be a point of contention for some.

One star is too much. We make the reservation because love argentinians food, but.... surprise!!!! No costumers at the place  (now understand why?) The food was not fresh, cold and extremely  expensive. Make me sick, can't sleep because the stomach. Want to forget and I can't.

This restaurant has authentic Argentinian food. The ambiance is wonderful. The food is presented beautifully. The steaks as expected were excellent. Servers and staff were friendly and attentive. Worth checking out when in the west loop.

Great steakhouse with a cozy but lively ambiance. I would highly recommend the Jalapeño popper empanadas as an appetizer; they do have some heat so don’t say I didn’t warn you. We also had the flank steak and the pork chops, they were phenomenal. We will be back with a larger group to try the parrillada. (Recommended for a group of 3-4 people)

My husband picked El Ché for dinner. We went early and sat in the bar. Our server was great, recommended items and drinks. The margarita is amazing. We tried a few items, but our favorite was the sweet breads, such a different presentation. We will definitely be back for more sweet breads!
My preferred place for argentinian food. Went there on a Friday I think. I've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. The place has a great feel to it.

Argentinian food... delicious. i had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here.
Amazing food and atmosphere.  Definite must try. Good date place.

We had an interesting experience at El Che. The food was very good. We ordered everything to share. We started with pimento cheese dip, and ordered the sirloin, short ribs (which are not your typical short ribs, just be warned ), asparagus side, sweet potato side dish, and an artichoke side. The sweet potato side dish I was a little worried about because it said it had caramel on top, and I was worried it would be too sweet. But it was delicious and very well balanced! The asparagus with Bearnaise sauce was also delicious! It had some fried shallots (I think?) on top and was really good. The sirloin was okay. The short ribs were mediocre. The waitress warned us that they were not what you are used to with short ribs. They were extremely fatty and had barely any meat on them. If you like fat, then these would be great for you. I had the dolce de leche ice cream for dessert and it was very good. So all in all the food was good. The service was another story. Our waitress was kind of standoffish and almost treated us as if we were idiots when asking questions about the menu. She was fine to have minimal interaction with, but I certainly wouldn't be rushing back here for the service. I'm not sure if that was a particularly bad day for her, or what, but we all kind of left their feeling put off, which is a bummer because we were very excited to try El Che out for the food. They do have valet. I did not see a lot of parking, so I'm not sure how promising parking yourself would be. Also, as a side note which I know really doesn't matter that much but overall affected our experience, the bathrooms were - I kid you not- 95 degrees. I legitimately was sweating after being in the bathroom for 2 minutes. I don't know if the heat was broken or what but it was unbearable.
There was nothing on this menu that was disappointing. If you’re a foodie, you’ll love this place.
Horrible! The worst experience in my life. A total scam!

I love small menus because it shows the chef is focusing on couple of items instead of having a wide assortment. This showed in the food which was wonderful. We had empendadas, filet mignon, gnochii, and flan. All tasted well cooked and carefully crafted. High recommend this place.
Bone marrow with toast is worth dying for. Yummy cocktails. And they have alfajores!
Great service, atmosphere, and food

My fiancé and I recently came here for Valentine's day dinner. The service was great and the meal was ultimately very good. The only disappointing aspect of the meal was the main course - we ordered a ribeye and were not blown away by the steak or the chimichurri. Given the nature of the restaurant, we expected that to be the best part of the meal. Still a good experience overall.
Great service, food and drinks in a very hip and beautiful setting. Love this place!
Dinner for two at the chefs table for my Birthday. Chef/Owner John cooked a 10 course meal! Exceptional.

Another recently discovered fine LATIN favorite of mine.  We went last week which was 'restaurant week in Chicago and the samplings of different entres were delightful.  I was impressed by how each different 'tapas' styled plate was more flavorful than the last. You can't go wrong with this place. Service was polite, timely and top notch.

Timely service and comfortable atmosphere. Steak, salmon, and shrimp dishes were well-seasoned and cooked perfectly- especially enjoyed the shrimp and polenta dish. Tres leches cake was not moistened by the milk mixture all the way through. Dishes can be pricey.
Great spot!! Our recommendation is to order to share. Order: chicken empanada, shrimp is a must. Drinks: Negroni and Malbec tinto
Beautiful decor, great service, outstanding food and cocktails. Went for restuarant week. The prix fixe menu was perfect and my choices were delicious. A great experience all around!

The ambiance is arresting, but dictates very little. Nothing appears out of the norm from an intimate meal to a small gathering. More importantly the small plates through the large plates and even the dessert are spectacular. The cocktails manage to keep pace with the demand for excellence. I shall return, without a doubt.

Very bland food. A seriously forgettable experience and the sad attempt at delicious Argentine cuisine makes me wonder why the reviews are anywhere as high as they are. In retrospect, it's quite mind-boggling that this restaurant and La Sirena Clandestina (a parallel failed execution of delectable Brazilian cuisine) survive in an area (West Loop) where so many creative and amazing chefs thrive and succeed. That being said, their version of alfajores cookies is quite good but not good enough to carry the weight of the overall mediocrity.
This place amazes me always. I have been there about 4 times. The food and service is always great.  Would highly recommend it for any type of event.
Expensive, but the steaks are great. Service is excellent, the restaurant is cozy and comfortable.
We signed a contract, left a credit card, and the owner canceled the party. It was for 15 people, for Saturday. Just not professional!

Love the outdoor seating.  Stopped in for a quick bite in the bar area.  Such a pretty atmosphere.The oysters were so good grilled.  The gnocchi with summer squash was delicious as were the hotlinks. Loved my Paloma drink and my baby loved his Rum Manhattan. Service was very good and the restaurant is so beautiful inside and out,  live plants everywhere is very nice touch. Check it out. You will be pleased. Stopped in for another bite. Loved the steak,  polenta, oysters and cookie. Yummy!!

Service and hostess were top knock notch. We had fantastic cocktails and the food was perfectly executed. The server was only there when needed but otherwise didn't interject during the meal. The bone marrow was maybe a bit over done, but everything else was great.
Definitely get the parrillada (best sweetbreads and Morcilla I've had in a while). The grilled oysters and pimento cheese were also both awesome.
Meat platter was awesome, good drinks and ambience. Another great addition to the west loop.

Overall excellent night out for our large party.  Staff was very attentive and educated on the menu. We had consumed a solid sampling of the menu and while most entrees were excellent, the sweet potato and carrot sides could have used a little less char on them to the point where they could have been recognizable.
Very Chic place. Went for an Xmas party. Tried Everything. All of it was Sensational.

I guess before I post I should start with a disclaimer...i love steak...i love authentic cuisine...and unfortunately...im from Philadelphia. Now that thats out of the way...i was disappointed with El Che...Empanada barely warm in the middle like they slapped old refrigerated dry short rib in the middle...short ribs on the bone....chewy...i mean im sorry but in Philadelphia we go to the Italian Market and pick up premium cuts of beef...this meal should have been served with skirt steak...its just common sense...if you want to do short ribs...braise them...have them fall off the bone...dont give a chewy cut that I have to naw at in a crowded restaurant. Gnocchi...boring....It just didnt feel fresh...for the prices I expected little pillows with a deep rich pan fry. Nothing felt that premium...even the wine was Ok...for 80 bucks...in Philly...thats a 7 course dinner with foie gras and hanger steak and monk fish...but hey...i guess thats why I live in Philly. 3 stars for ambiance and friendliness.
Happened to visit on the first Tuesday of the month and did the Prix fix meal! Great food and great ambiance!
Delicious food awesome service great drinks
Overpriced food drinks suck
Great food, atmosphere and service! Loved the trout, their salads, empanadas and the Sweet Potatoes!!!!!

Really wonderful experience here. Had a large party show up and the service was spot on and very attentive. From the decor and ambiance to the food, it was a great time.  I really enjoyed my steak. It was done perfectly. And also the cocktails were perfection.  This is a great place for a date, special occasion or a  business meal. High recommend!

The chef and all the staff are amazing and friendly, we were looking at pictures of his dog before the night was through. Expect to spend a lot of time here, but it's incredibly worth it. Do it. The food was amazing. Everything that we ate was so full of flavor. Even the broccoli was to die for!! I actually had seconds! ...of broccoli! !  The server was great as well. Very attentive.
Great food and alcohol selection, just a little pricey.
Very creative menu and impressive wine list.  The asparagus and branzino are a must.
Wow!! The food was outstanding. The staff friendly and attentive. Highly recommend El Che Bar. We will be back.
I’ve only had cocktails here. But they’re very good with a friendly bartender and relaxed scene. Pricing is similar to other chi-town bars ($13 cocktail)

First place I've ever given 5 stars. I did because the food was unique, well plated and delicious. The drinks were great and the wine selection is perfect for the food pairings and the service was amazing. Water glasses were never empty, they transferred out plates and silverware quickly and dessert was delicious. Definitely try this place. Bone marrow recommended

The food is extremely well crafted and the cocktails are exceptional. The ambiance is pleasant, with a darker atmosphere that is great for a date night. I highly recommend the beef shortribs, which are exceptionally prepared and feature a terrific sauce over the top to add a nice flair.  The service was friendly without being intrusive, and they were very good about refilling water regularly.  The portion sizes are great to share or to keep for yourself, although some items do get pricey as well (e.g. a 90 dollar steak). All-in-all, very well worth the trip!
Just a great place to eat meat!
Loved this place when we first went in 2016 but the quality has definitely gone downhill. Steaks were over cooked, dry and kind of chewey.
Decent food - liked pimento cheese a lot, and asparagus was great if less than healthy.  Didn't love service and prices seemed a tad higher than necessary

Had a date night there and it was good. They let us on quickly although we didn't make any reservation. It was Thursday night and not too busy night for them at that time. However, it took awhile for the server to reach our table and took our first order. But once he got to us, he assisted us well.  The Japanese sweet potatoes were excellent. We really enjoyed it as much as the oyster. I always prefer raw oysters but their grilled ones were delicious. I ordered the fish and it was fantastic. The steak that we got was so so though. Overall, we enjoyed our visit.
Fantastic food

On a rainy Thursday night, service was slow and uninviting. The tequila and mezcal drinks had good flavor. Cooked oysters were good, but not drive out of your way. Sweet potatoes are worth a try. The steak was gummy,as in chewy. The branzino fish was ok, it had good flavor. Over all the presentation and plating were lackluster. It's overpriced for the quality and service.

Great place for dinner and drinks. Had their $44 prix fixe (available every Tues) which was absolutely delicious. Ate at the bar and had the pleasure of being served by Jacy the bar manager/tender. She was super friendly and gave tips on which bars to also check out as I am not from Chicago.
An amazing meal all around. Service was impecable. Food was stellar! Great wines as well. I would highly recommend it to anyone in Chicago.
Interior has great atmosphere, everything we ordered was great and the service was very good. They have a sidewalk patio as well, but we sat inside this time
Love the cocktails here

Nice little Argentinian steakhouse.  The staff and service are fantastic, and took care of us very well.  They have a fantastic selection of cocktails and wine. The Argentinian wine suggested to us was delicious.  The food, overall, was good, but I was a little disappointed in the porterhouse our table ordered.  It was a little overcooked versus what we ordered.
John. The morcilla. The empanadas. Steak. Fantastic service. Thank you.
Cute little place with great food! Definitely get the veggie sides as well as the meat.
SWEETBREADS in the barbecue platter. The platter was enough for three. Sweetbreads, chorizo, blood sausage, flank steak. Well prepared and tasty. Waiter was not great but o.k. The food was 5 stars.
Loved the bar and drink selection!
Lovely. Great service and food

I had reservations and still had to wait for an hour. As we waited the host comped champagne for our group for the extended wait which was a nice touch.  The food is really good, service is slow which makes sense why we waited so long before seated.  The ambience is nice and may return one day. Hopefully they can step up the service.

Went with a group of four for dinner. We decided to get several dishes and share family style. We ordered: Los Pinguinos Punch: Comes in a fun penguin pitcher. Would compare it to a red sangria. Not too sweet, a little tart. Fugazetta: Delicious, almost a cross between a quiche and pizza. Herbed Parisian Gnocchi: This was decadent and the sauce was amazing. I would go back for this and eat it as a full meal or side. Wood Roasted Amish Chicken: really great serving, meat was moist and flavorful. Veggies were cooked to perfection. Great flavors all around. Glad I tried it.
One of the best meals I’ve ever had! The steak was divine.
Wheelchair accessible but no automatic door with push plate. The space is cozy and inviting while being sexy. Service was attentive and friendly. Prices high but on par with neighborhood.
Great dining experience. Attentive staff. Highly recommended booking the chef's counter.

We tried the kale and gruyere empanada, beef Picadillo empanada, Parisian Gnocchi, charred carrots, thin cut pork chops, and churros. Everything was fantastic. If I was to pick only one to recommend, it would be the Parisian Gnocchi. Excellent and melt in your mouth.

Went on a Thursday night with my wife and a couple of friends. The restaurant was highly rated on OpenTable and other websites, so I chose this for our dinner. The reception was nice and attentive/friendly. The ambiance was okay - the chairs seemed cheap and where uncomfortable. They didn't even look hip, which was a surprise for the area. Light bulbs in the fixtures were mismatched and different color temperatures, which is a small detail, but something I noticed immediately, and set the ambiance to a cheap/builder-grade decor. Service was not good. Our waiter was attentive and accommodating upon arrival, getting drink orders and coming back to take our order. After that, we didn't see him until the end of the meal when he handed us our check, even when we were obviously looking for him. He never checked in on us so we didn't have anyone to report to when we had issues with our meal. We ordered the pork chops which were burnt to a crisp and had a pretty bad mustard sauce on it. The chimichurri was good, and the dried out/burnt pork chop needed a lot of it, and the peanuts that were on it looked like they were just thrown on. Bizarre for a $28 entrée. The NY strip steak was cooked fine, but it was horribly under seasoned. For $58 it should be an great steak. But I did not care for it, and I'm a steak lover. The other small plates were unremarkable. The best thing I ate were the Brussel sprouts.  As I didn't want to make a scene with our dinner guests present, I kept my mouth shut and didn't complain about the poor service nor when I couldn't get a second drink order in. I flagged down one of the food runners, not realizing it wasn't our waiter. Eventually, another server came to our table, and I was able to order a drink, but it took nearly 20 minutes to receive. It was a pretty disappointing experience, especially considering it was a $260 tab for 4 diners. With as many amazing dining options as there are in the West Loop, I highly doubt I'll return to El Che Bar.
Awesome food and creative cocktails. Not a huge menu, but everything we had was delicious and well-done. Good service, a cool ambiance and interesting decor made this a fantastic spot for a date.
Excellent service. Delicious food. Beautiful atmosphere.
Chef Counter.
Nice restaurant with BYOB policy!
Great service and menu
Excellent service, food, and drinks.
Great Japanese sweet potatoes and carrots. And might be the best gnocchi I've ever had!

I had the Old Fashioned and morning wife had an Aperol spritz. Nothing crazy taste wise, but both were presented very properly.  Food wise we had small plates of Brussels Sprouts in some sort of cashew glaze and then a Gnocchi dish with goat cheese, pomegranates and mushrooms. Both were fantastic and creative dishes.  Not cheap, but worth it for date night. Also, wine list was better than average and not ridiculously priced.
Great food, but $$$.
This place is great for a cocktail. Good atmosphere, friendly and knowledgeable bartender, fantastic decor,  but the food was a bit over priced.
Had to send a dish back because it was so poorly prepared.
Everything was perfect!
amazing!
Fun Place to go.
Great Flame broiled menu!
Very good place to have dinner with friends. Great food and cocktails. Winr selection is good as well.
The menu is ever changing and after 3 visits I've never had anything that I didn't love. Definitely get the bbq pork ribs if they're on the menu!
Super delicious spot!! Great service, we ordered half the menu and there was nothing we didn't like!!!
Holy cow... no really amazing. From the drinks to the wood fired menu... amazing !!!

El Che Bar was a wonderful Saturday evening date/birthday celebration spot. We loved the atmosphere, background music, and all-around service. The food was delicious including empanadas, which we were given complimentary since our food was taking longer than expected!! The pork chops and flatiron steak were exceptional. The presentation of the praline affogato dessert was awesome and very tasty. I would highly recommend this place for an Argentinian spin to food as well some great Argentinian Malbec!

Really really cool joint. You should expect it to be arrogant in its approach and demeanor from looks but it's anything but. Good choice of drinks and really reasonable for the area. Friendly staff totally worth seeking out for a visit.

This place didn't disappoint. The food is creative and outstanding. Everything is cooked with wood burning ovens and grills. The flavor is deep and complex. The service is well trained and heads up. Our server recognized that we were on a date, and kept his service attentive and minimal. That's a great sign of being pro. The environment is beautiful, but not distracting. This is a great place to impress, and experience something unique.
Bring lots of cash and your meat appetite.
This place is amazing!
Food was outstanding and the service even better.  Will definitely go back.
Great drinks, food and service. A little pricey, but we always enjoy it.
Overall, excellent meal. Beautiful space and interesting shared plates. Dessert was a highlight as it was delicious and fun to look at. Highly recommend this spot in the WL!
Energetic restaurant with spot on food and cocktails.
My new favorite spot in Chicago. Sour tropical campari cocktails are fantastic. Don't miss the pork chops.
Great atmosphere and awesome food!
I came here for restaurant week. The server made good drink recommendations and the food was pretty good.
Excellent food and wine selection.  Shout out to Hugo for being wonderful at his job.

Everything was great. Service was top notch. We decided to get a bunch of plates and share and it turned out awesome. We were able to add an additional item to the dishes so that we each could get a taste. Highly suggest the lamb ribs and quail!
Increible. The best morcilla I've ever had. Creative cocktails and desserts top it all off. Great for a drink and a bite or a full-on date night.

The menu was so good we literally ordered one of everything for the table.  I've eaten here a few times and I can't find anything to Complain about. Bring a date or a few friends but come hungry and try some cocktails.
Food is great, service was awesome, great wine selection and desserts! Would definitely come here again
Real wood fire grill. Amazing steaks. Fresh chimichurri.  Best service.

Amazing food and ambience. Everything was fantastic, but the salmon was the best I've ever had. I knew the chef from La Sirena wouldn't let us down, and he most definitely did not. Can't wait to return!
Fantastic, authentic. But pricey.

Went here for a birthday and was a little surprised. The food was good but not great. I really expected it to be a lot better.
Morcilla is to die for... literally it will clog your arteries with amazingNess.  The sweetbreads are my favorite savory dish this side of the Amazon.  Enjoy!
Improportionally expensive to good
My new favorite in Chicago. Great steaks and my wife loved the salmon. Nice wine list and great vibe. Cool spot!
Great food, upscale atmosphere, lively open kitchen near the back

I'd rate it a 3 1/2 if possible.  The service was flat out awful.  Waitstaff seemed very overwhelmed.  There was easily 10 busboys to 1 waiter  Food was hit and miss, but definitely shows potential.  Get the Ice Cream Sandwich.  I'll go back but won't be in a hurry.

The food and ambience is very nice. We had the oysters, pickled shrimp and beets as starter. The gnocchi was fabulous, nice and fluffy. We shared as entrees - the sweetbreads, short ribs, and the filet. I really loved the sweetbreads. The sauce on the filet was amazing, great mustard flavor. The filet was cooked perfectly.
Loved the ambience and service and the food is excellent!!!  The oysters, scamorza, morcilla, Lamb, pork and onions are a must! Congrats team El Che!

It's new so the Google profile isn't complete here. But it's definitely worth checking out. The entrance is a little hidden in the Checker Cab building. They use a wall of flames in the kitchen which gives the food a subtle smokey flavor.
